MLIS Fees Solution Design
 
## 1. Objective
Deliver MLIS Fee support across Quote, Submission (Opportunity), and Policy flows with the following UX model:
- Fee control is managed on Opportunity (Submission)
- Underwriter uses a button action similar to Edit Premium / Limit of Indemnity
- Button opens a modal containing fee fields and a range slider
- Changes drive Fee__c creation/update rules for NB, MTA, and Cancellation
 
## 2. Proposed UX Design
### 2.1 Entry Point
- Add an Opportunity quick action/button: Manage MLIS Fee
- Visibility: Underwriter profiles/permission set only
- Hidden/disabled for portal users
 
### 2.2 Modal Design
Fields in modal:
- Enable MLIS Fee toggle (on/off)
- Transaction context selector:
  - New Business
  - MTA
  - Cancellation
- Fee amount input (currency)
- Fee range slider (min/max constrained by governance)
- Override reason (mandatory when fee differs from default)
- Read-only system default fee (effective-dated)
 
Modal behavior:
- On open, read effective-dated default for selected transaction context
- Pre-populate slider and amount with current active value
- Slider and amount stay synchronized
- Save validates min/max range and lock rules
 
### 2.3 Locking Rules
- If Opportunity is Live: modal opens read-only or save blocked with message
- If policy is Forced: modal opens read-only or save blocked with message
- Existing values remain unchanged when lock conditions apply
 
## 3. Data and Logic Design
### 3.1 Fee Source of Truth
- Effective-dated fee configuration remains source of default value
- Opportunity override (if present and valid) takes precedence
 
### 3.2 Fee__c Creation/Update Rule
- Create one Fee__c per qualifying transaction event:
  - NB
  - MTA
  - Cancellation
- Avoid duplicates per transaction instance
- Store:
  - Type = MLIS Fee
  - Amount, currency
  - Transaction context
  - Non-returnable flag
 
### 3.3 Non-Returnable and Correction Rule
- MLIS fee is non-returnable in all cancellation outputs
- For internal cancel-and-reissue correction path:
  - no MLIS fee charge
  - no MLIS fee return line
 
## 4. Integration Points
- Quote Results: show MLIS Fee line + updated totals
- Quote Summary: show MLIS Fee line + updated totals
- Documents (where premium/total appears):
  - Quote Document
  - Specimen Policy Document
  - Final Draft
  - Policy Document
  - Debit Note
- Optional BDX mapping controlled by feature toggle
 
## 5. Security and Audit
- Underwriter-only edit access on Opportunity
- Portal users read-only/no edit for fee controls
- Track audit details for each override change:
  - user
  - timestamp
  - old value
  - new value
  - reason
 
## 6. Acceptance Highlights
- Underwriter can manage fee from Opportunity button modal
- Slider and amount remain synchronized and validated
- Locks enforced for Live Opportunity and Forced Policy
- MLIS fee appears correctly in quote views and in-scope docs
- Cancellation refunds exclude MLIS fee
- Cancel-and-reissue internal correction does not apply MLIS fee
 
## 7. Delivery Components
- Opportunity UI:
  - quick action/button
  - modal component with slider and validation
- Service layer:
  - retrieve default fee by transaction/effective date
  - apply override precedence
  - create/update Fee__c with duplicate prevention
- Downstream rendering:
  - quote/result/summary updates
  - document merge updates
  - optional BDX mapping
- Testing:
  - unit + integration + UAT scenarios
 
